{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:22:13.279836+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ca886e6501062ae49242c9393da158c273a90050)", "id": "lc_d9fea9d3-6e1e-4968-a1e1-8f3423ae0cb0"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Build and execute ffmpeg subprocess calls based on a profile dict.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef build_ffmpeg_command(profile: dict, input_path: Path, output_path: Path) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Translate a profile dict into an ffmpeg argv list.\"\"\"\n    cmd = [\"ffmpeg\", \"-i\", str(input_path)]\n\n    container = profile[\"container\"]\n    if container == \"gif\":\n        # Single-pass palette generation. See profiles.toml note about quality.\n        fps = profile.get(\"fps\", 12)\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\", \"480:-1\")\n        cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"fps={fps},scale={scale}:flags=lanczos\"]\n    else:\n        video_codec = profile[\"video_codec\"]\n        audio_codec = profile[\"audio_codec\"]\n        cmd += [\"-c:v\", video_codec, \"-c:a\", audio_codec]\n        if \"video_bitrate\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-b:v\", profile[\"video_bitrate\"]]\n        if \"crf\" in profile:\n            cmd += [\"-crf\", str(profile[\"crf\"])]\n        scale = profile.get(\"scale\")\n        if scale and scale != \"source\":\n            cmd += [\"-vf\", f\"scale={scale}\"]\n\n    cmd.append(str(output_path))\n    return cmd\n\n\ndef run(cmd: list[str]) -> int:\n    return subprocess.call(cmd)\n", "id": "lc_ef536d54-af69-45e3-ad17-bb76e8999dea"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "12d8e9ec-bdce-457a-a137-62025f6d3362", "tool_call_id": "call_00_syJCjkbqeUT3wybrERKH9118", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:22:19.282756+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository's `profiles.toml` file, the `vidpack` command offers three encoding profiles:\n\n| Profile name | Container | Video codec | Audio codec |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **`web`** | `.mp4` | `libx264` (H.264) | `aac` |\n| **`archive`** | `.mkv` | `libx265` (H.265 / HEVC) | `flac` |\n| **`gif`** | `.gif` | N/A (palette-based GIF generation) | N/A (no audio) |\n\n### How a profile is selected\n\nThe user passes the profile name as a positional argument:\n\n```\nvidpack <profile> <input> [-o output]\n```\n\nThe CLI (`src/vidpack/cli.py`) calls `profiles.load_profile(args.profile)`, which looks up the name in `profiles.toml`. If the name is not found, it prints the available names.\n\n### Details from the codebase\n\n- **`profiles.toml`** – defines the three profiles shown above.\n- **`src/vidpack/runner.py`** – translates each profile into an `ffmpeg` command line.\n  - For `web`/`archive` (non-GIF): sets `-c:v` / `-c:a` to the specified codecs and applies optional bitrate/CRF/scale parameters.\n  - For `gif`: uses a single-pass palette approach with a `-vf` filter chain for FPS and scale (no audio).\n\nSo the three profiles are **web** (MP4/H.264/AAC), **archive** (MKV/H.265/FLAC), and **gif** (GIF, no audio).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 519, "prompt_tokens": 4931, "total_tokens": 5450, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 140, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4480}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 4480, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 451}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "280e730f-d610-4f44-a34c-03ef8354dd5e", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f6-fca0-78d1-b925-d64e54b0e2de-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4931, "output_tokens": 519, "total_tokens": 5450, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4480}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 140}}}}]}}}
